File: A PCR test for the coronavirus. AFP/Ina Fassbender JOHANNESBURG - The NICD said 399 new Covid-19 infections have been recorded. Sadly, nine more people have died in the last 24 to 48 hours. Gauteng is leading in infections with 154 cases. READ: Europe to see 'high levels' of Covid this summer: WHO It's followed by the Western Cape with 86 new cases. The rest of the provinces recorded less than 50 infections. Just over 11,000 tests were conducted and the positivity rate stands at 3.6 percent. #COVID19 UPDATE: 11,114 tests were conducted in the last 24hrs, with 399 new cases, which represents a 3.6% positivity rate. Today @HealthZA reports 29 deaths; of which 9 occurred in the past 24–48 hrs. Total fatalities are 101,793 to date: https://t.co/H7iew0IgEw pic.twitter.com/O9GpYNT29k